criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  age between 18 and 60 years;

          -  female and male;

          -  patients with SLE, according to the revised classification criteria of the ACR
             (Arthritis Rheum, 1997) with current or previous joint activity (arthritis or
             arthralgia;

          -  patients with established RA according to ACR classification criteria (Arthritis
             Rheum, 1988)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  changing the dose or drug-based immunosuppression in the last 3 months.

          -  corticosteroid pulse therapy in the last 30 days;

          -  infiltration with corticosteroids at hand in the last 3 months;

          -  previous surgery in the joints studied;

          -  irreducible deformity of the joints studied;

          -  overlap with other joint diseases or collagen;

          -  chiropractic diabetic;

          -  hypothyroidism
